[gd_scene load_steps=7 format=3 uid="uid://d7ply2cmpb3n5"]

; Fixture: boundary shell policy-compare
; Purpose: side-by-side visual comparison of all three BoundaryCrossingPolicy values.
;   Three identical spheres (radius 2.5) at X=-4 / X=0 / X=+4.
;   All use CrossingEvent, BiasDirection=Up, BiasStrength=0.15.
;   Only CrossingPolicy differs:
;     Left  (X=-4): EntryOnly (=0)  — one upward kink at sphere entry
;     Centre (X=0): EntryAndExit (=2) — upward kink at entry AND exit → ~double displacement
;     Right  (X=+4): ExitOnly (=1)  — ray enters straight, kinks upward at exit only
;
; Expected visual (DebugLogCrossings=true on all three):
;   Left column: dots behind left shell appear shifted down ≈2.7 units (one entry event).
;   Centre column: dots shifted down ≈5.4 units (two events, entry+exit compound).
;   Right column: dots shifted down ≈2.7 units (one exit event); shift position differs from Left
;     because the kink occurs at the far side of the sphere rather than the near side.
;     The right-column dot may appear slightly blurrier at the shell rim vs. the left column.
;
; Debug log (per ray through each shell):
;   Left:   1× entry event, layer=0 name='BoundaryShell_EntryOnly'
;   Centre: 1× entry + 1× exit, layer=1 name='BoundaryShell_EntryAndExit'
;   Right:  1× exit event, layer=2 name='BoundaryShell_ExitOnly'
;
; Start-inside check: camera at Z=8, all shells radius=2.5 centred at Z=0. Camera outside all. ✓
; Ordering: snap indices follow scene tree order → Left=0, Centre=1, Right=2.

